Package ca.mcgill.ecse211.project

Class Resources

  • java.lang.Object
    • ca.mcgill.ecse211.project.Resources
  • public class Resources
extends java.lang.Object
    This class is used to define static resources in one place for easy access and to avoid cluttering the rest of the codebase. Integrate this carefully with your existing Resources class (See below for where to add your code from your current Resources file). The order in which things are declared matters!
    Author:
    Younes Boubekeur
